{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":120580,"duration_api_ms":102024,"num_turns":21,"result":"```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Replaced the silent .ok() in snapshot_plan_hash() (fs.rs:2570) with an explicit match that distinguishes file-not-found (returns None silently, as expected for milestones without a snapshot) from all other errors (corrupt JSON, permission failures, etc.), which now emit a tracing::warn with the milestone_id and error details before returning None. This ensures operators can detect corrupted snapshots that silently prevent plan_hash auto-population, without changing the function's return type or caller behavior.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes but will appear in cargo fmt --check across the full workspace.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Replaced .ok().and_then(|s| s.plan_hash) in snapshot_plan_hash() with a match expression: Ok(snapshot) extracts plan_hash, Err(AppError::Io(NotFound)) returns None silently, all other Err variants log tracing::warn with milestone_id and error before returning None\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated doc comment on snapshot_plan_hash() to document the new warning behavior for unexpected errors\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Ran cargo test (683 unit + 351 lib + 128 integration + 1 doc = 1163 total, 0 failed), cargo clippy -- -D warnings (clean), cargo fmt --check on src/adapters/fs.rs (clean)\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 683 unit tests passed, 0 failed; 1163 total across all test targets, 0 failed\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: src/adapters/fs.rs clean; only pre-existing formatting diffs in unrelated tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs\",\n    \"Match arm Err(AppError::Io(ref e)) if e.kind() == NotFound correctly handles the normal case where no snapshot file exists yet (e.g., before any persist_plan call)\",\n    \"Match arm Err(err) catches CorruptRecord (malformed JSON), Io errors other than NotFound (permission denied, disk full), and any other AppError variants, logging all with milestone_id and error message\",\n    \"tracing::warn uses structured fields (milestone_id, error) consistent with existing tracing usage in br_process.rs and process_backend.rs\",\n    \"Function return type and caller contract unchanged — callers still receive Option<String> and treat None as 'no plan_hash available'\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"dc6aa508-19dd-4e12-bdf9-726d7fd9c018","total_cost_usd":0.7870662499999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":16,"cache_creation_input_tokens":48405,"cache_read_input_tokens":761610,"output_tokens":4146,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":48405,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":16,"outputTokens":4146,"cacheReadInputTokens":761610,"cacheCreationInputTokens":48405,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7870662499999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"72c9e0fc-3a4c-42ad-97bd-d43430a615bf"}
